<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,287,751,776]" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">Comments.</emphasis>
This taxon was described as a distinct species from 
<collectingCountry box="[883,964,751,776]" name="Spain" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">Melilla</collectingCountry>
on the basis of specimens with very long pubescence (
<figureCitation box="[302,371,788,813]" captionStart="FIGURES 1 – 11" captionStartId="4.[151,264,1821,1844]" captionTargetBox="[167,1431,212,1789]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,195,1797]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURES 1 – 11. Habitus of Singilis bicolor - group. 1 — S. bicolor; 2 — S. alternans; 3 — S. soror melillensis (Taurirt); 4 — S. soror riffensis syn. n., Paratype (Isaguen); 5 – 6 — S. soror riffensis syn. n. (Ketama); 7 — S. soror s. str. (15 km SE Berkane); 8 — S. soror s. str. = S. pardoi syn. n., Paratype (El Haraig); 9 — S. soror s. str. (Oudjda); 10 — S. soror oranensis ssp. n. Holotype; 11 — S. soror oranensis Paratype." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/291795/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">Fig 3</figureCitation>
). No other differential characters were found between this taxon and other populations. 
<collectorName box="[151,277,823,848]" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">Therefore I</collectorName>
propose to consider 
<taxonomicName box="[511,659,823,848]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Singilis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="melillensis">
<emphasis box="[511,659,823,848]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">S. melillensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a subspecies of 
<taxonomicName box="[872,958,824,848]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Singilis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="271" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="soror">
<emphasis box="[872,958,824,848]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="271">S. soror</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Aedeagus as in fig. 18.
</materialsCitation>
